        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:a055f89c-234f-4b4a-b6ff-23d23067eb57 ;
    align:confidence "0.95"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The definitions are almost identical, differing only in minor phrasing and the inclusion of a URI in dpv-aiact. The core meaning – describing the intended use as defined by the provider through documentation – is precisely aligned."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:IntendedPurpose ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/legal/eu/aiact#IntendedPurpose> .

align:344eaefd-8d8a-45f4-85f9-b283070caaa2 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:a055f89c-234f-4b4a-b6ff-23d23067eb57 ;
    align:confidence "0.85"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts relate to monitoring after deployment. However, the `dpv-aiact` concept explicitly frames this within the context of the EU AI Act's requirements for a *plan*, suggesting a more formal and legally mandated process than the general 'activity' described by AIDOC. While highly related and often overlapping in practice, they aren’t interchangeable due to this difference in scope and purpose."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:PostMarketMonitoringActivity ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/legal/eu/aiact#PostMarketMonitoringPlan> .

align:3ed7fe0a-0c22-401f-922e-20d1306f97f6 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:a055f89c-234f-4b4a-b6ff-23d23067eb57 ;
    align:confidence "0.95"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "The descriptions are almost identical. The AIDOC concept describes *activity* of using data for validation while dpv-aiact defines the *data itself*. This is a subtle difference that doesn't prevent interchangeability in many contexts; both fundamentally refer to the same thing – the data used for AI model evaluation and tuning."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:exactMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:DataValidation ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/legal/eu/aiact#ValidationData> .

align:483cc4ab-82c3-4a61-b625-8ad7cce346f6 a prov:Entity,
        align:Mapping ;
    prov:wasAttributedTo align:LLMAlignmentBot ;
    prov:wasGeneratedBy align:a055f89c-234f-4b4a-b6ff-23d23067eb57 ;
    align:confidence "0.88"^^xsd:float ;
    align:rationale "Both concepts refer to a Declaration of Conformity document. However, the `dpv-aiact` concept explicitly ties this declaration to the EU AI Act and Article 47, making it specific to AI systems. The `AIDOC` concept is more general, encompassing declarations for various standards. While highly similar and often overlapping in practical application, they aren't strictly interchangeable due to the legal context of the AI Act."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:DeclarationOfConformity ;
    align:target <https://w3id.org/dpv/legal/eu/aiact#EUDeclarationOfConformity> .

