    align:rationale "Both concepts relate to monitoring AI systems post-deployment. However, the dpv-aiact concept explicitly frames this activity within a legal/regulatory context (EU AIACT) and emphasizes corrective/preventive actions stemming from identified issues. The AIDOC concept is more general, simply describing performance & behavior monitoring. While highly related and often overlapping in practice, they aren't interchangeable due to the regulatory focus of dpv-aiact."^^xsd:string ;
    align:relation skos:closeMatch ;
    align:source aidoc:PostMarketMonitoringActivity ;
